 Results will be reviewed by the study physician for compliance to inclusion and exclusion criteria.

 The screening visit will also include a review of foods to avoid during run-in and study participation.

 Once lab results from the screening visit come back and are determined to be satisfactory for inclusion, the subject will be called and instructed to start dietary restrictions.

 The first stool collection (Day -1) will occur after two weeks of dietary compliance.

